* Gtk#

** Gtk# in a nutshell

  <a href="http://gtk-sharp.sourceforge.net">Gtk#</a> (also refered as 
  gtk-sharp) is a C# language binding for the 
  <a href="http://www.gtk.org">Gtk+</a> toolkit. It is called to be the
  'de facto' GUI toolkit for the <a href="http://www.go-mono.org">Mono
  Project</a> and for the future <a href="http://www.gnome.org">GNOME</a>
  apps based in Mono, as the Gtk+ is for most of the GNOME apps written in
  C.  

** API of Gtk#

  The API is browsable 
  <a href="http://primates.ximian.com/~tvgm/gtk-sharp-docs/">here</a>

** Where to learn more.

  Visit the <a href="http://gtk-sharp.sourceforge.net">Gtk# Project</a>.
  The <a href="http://www.go-mono.org/faq">Mono FAQ</a> has some useful
  information too.

